      "content": "Certainly! Below is a complete HTML file that creates a simple A-Frame VR scene featuring an animated cheeseburger and allows for WASD movement. You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser that supports WebVR.\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Animated Cheeseburger VR</title>\n    <script src=\"https://aframe.io/releases/1.2.0/aframe.min.js\"></script>\n    <style>\n        body { margin: 0; }\n        a-scene { height: 100vh; }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <a-scene>\n        <a-assets>\n            <img id=\"burgerTexture\" src=\"https://example.com/cheeseburger.png\" />\n        </a-assets>\n\n        <a-sky color=\"#87CEEB\"></a-sky>\n\n        <a-entity id=\"burger\" position=\"0 1 -3\" rotation=\"0 0 0\" scale=\"1 1 1\">\n            <a-box position=\"0 0.5 0\" depth=\"0.5\" height=\"0.2\" width=\"1\" color=\"#FFD700\" animation=\"property: position; to: 0 1.2 -3; dir: alternate; dur: 1000; loop: true\"></a-box>\n            <a-sphere position=\"0 0.5 0\" radius=\"0.4\" color=\"#FF6347\" animation=\"property: position; to: 0 1.1 -3; dir: alternate; dur: 1000; loop: true\"></a-sphere>\n            <a-sphere position=\"0 0.7 0\" radius=\"0.35\" color=\"#FFFACD\" animation=\"property: position; to: 0 1.15 -3; dir: alternate; dur: 1000; loop: true\"></a-sphere>\n            <a-sphere position=\"0 0.9 0\" radius=\"0.3\" color=\"#8B4513\" animation=\"property: position; to: 0 1.05 -3; dir: alternate; dur: 1000; loop: true\"></a-sphere>\n        </a-entity>\n\n        <a-entity camera look-controls position=\"0 1.6 0\">\n            <a-entity position=\"0 0 -1\" geometry=\"primitive: box; height: 0.1; width: 0.1; depth: 0.1\" material=\"color: red\"></a-entity>\n        </a-entity>\n\n        <a-entity id=\"cursor\" geometry=\"primitive: ring; radiusInner: 0.02; radiusOuter: 0.03\" material=\"color: red; shader: flat\" position=\"0 0 -1\" cursor=\"fuse: false; maxDistance: 10\"></a-entity>\n    </a-scene>\n\n    <script>\n        // WASD movement controls\n        const camera = document.querySelector('[camera]');\n        const speed = 0.1;\n\n        document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {\n            switch (event.key) {\n                case 'w':\n                    camera.object3D.position.z -= speed;\n                    break;\n                case 's':\n                    camera.object3D.position.z += speed;\n                    break;\n                case 'a':\n                    camera.object3D.position.x -= speed;\n                    break;\n                case 'd':\n                    camera.object3D.position.x += speed;\n                    break;\n            }\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n### Instructions:\n1. Replace the `src` attribute of the `<img>` tag in the `<a-assets>` section with the URL of your cheeseburger image.\n2. Save the code in a file with a `.html` extension (e.g., `burger-vr.html`).\n3. Open the file in a web browser that supports A-Frame and WebVR (like Chrome or Firefox).\n4. Use the WASD keys to move around the scene.\n\nThis code creates a simple animated cheeseburger using basic shapes and allows for movement within the VR scene. Enjoy your VR experience!"
